3. The pressure-correction schemes
Pressure-correction schemes are time-marching techniques composed of two sub-steps for each time step: the pressure is treated explicitly or ignored in the first sub-step and is corrected in the second one by projecting the provisional velocity onto the space H introduced in (2.2).
